SUMMARY:Deadline: Alicia Patterson Fellowship 2027 (Fund for Investigative 
 Journalism)
DESCRIPTION:Long-running fellowship for in-depth\, investigative written re
 porting on subjects of public interest\, now administered by the Fund for 
 Investigative Journalism after the foundation's December 2025 merger. For 
 seasoned reporters with a body of in-depth written work\; freelancers are 
 encouraged and staff journalists may apply if they take leave (part-time w
 ork is allowed during the fellowship\, full-time is not). Twelve-month fel
 lows produce four articles\, six-month fellows two. Decisions by end of 20
 26. Distinct from FIJ's regular reporting grants. No application fee.\n\nO
 rganisation: Fund for Investigative Journalism (Alicia Patterson Foundatio
 n program)\nLocation: Remote\; fellows may live anywhere\, but projects mu
 st be U.S.-focused for publication in American outlets\nAward: $40\,000 (1
 2-month fellowship) or $20\,000 (6-month fellowship)\, paid monthly\; cove
 rs living and reporting costs\nDuration: 6 or 12 months\, beginning early 
 2027\n\nMore: https://investigate.submittable.com/submit/355041/alicia-pat
 terson-fellowship-2027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=re
 ferral
